WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:23.615 --> 00:25.900
So stay with us,
because later this afternoon,

00:25.935 --> 00:28.186
we're lucky enough to be
talking to Anna Scott,

00:28.221 --> 00:29.986
Hollywood's biggest
star by far.

00:30.021 --> 00:33.331
Miss Scott's latest film is
once again topping the charts...

02:26.304 --> 02:30.708
Of course, I've seen her films and
always thought she was, well, fabulous.

02:30.743 --> 02:34.212
But, you know, a million, million
miles from the world I live in.

02:34.247 --> 02:36.565
Which is here, Notting Hill.

02:36.600 --> 02:38.509
My favorite bit of London.

02:38.544 --> 02:40.383
There's the market on weekdays

02:40.418 --> 02:43.125
selling every fruit
and vegetable known to man.

02:43.521 --> 02:45.907
Rock hard bananas,
five for a pound!

02:45.942 --> 02:48.258
The tattoo parlor
with a guy outside

02:48.293 --> 02:51.831
who got drunk and now can't
remember why he chose "I love Ken. "

02:52.630 --> 02:55.967
The radical hairdressers, where
everyone comes out looking like

02:56.002 --> 02:59.204
the Cookie Monster,
whether they want to or not.

02:59.239 --> 03:01.204
And then, suddenly,
it's the weekend

03:01.239 --> 03:04.209
and from break of day hundreds
of stalls appear out of nowhere

03:04.244 --> 03:07.177
filling Portobello Road,
right up to Notting Hill Gate.

03:07.212 --> 03:10.982
And wherever you look thousands of
people are buying millions of antiques,

03:11.017 --> 03:14.930
some genuine,
and some not quite so genuine.

03:16.421 --> 03:19.724
And what's great is that lots of friends
have ended up in this part of London.

03:19.759 --> 03:23.226
That's Tony, for example,
architect turned chef

03:23.261 --> 03:26.698
who recently invested all the money
he ever earned in a new restaurant.

03:26.733 --> 03:29.468
And so, this is where
I spend my days and years,

03:29.503 --> 03:32.168
in this small village
in the middle of the city,

03:32.203 --> 03:35.338
in a house with a blue door that
my wife and I bought together

03:35.373 --> 03:39.227
before she left me for a man who
looked exactly like Harrison Ford.

03:39.262 --> 03:43.081
And where I now lead a strange
half-life with a lodger called...

03:43.116 --> 03:44.082
Spike?

03:48.953 --> 03:50.186
Hi.

03:50.221 --> 03:53.458
You couldn't help me with an incredibly
important decision, could you?

03:53.493 --> 03:55.377
Is this important
in comparison to, let's say,

03:55.412 --> 03:57.227
whether they should cancel
Third World debt?

03:57.262 --> 04:00.798
That's right. I'm at last going
out on a date with the great Janine

04:00.833 --> 04:02.934
and I just wanna be sure
I've picked the right T-shirt.

04:02.969 --> 04:05.414
What are the choices?
Well, wait for it.

04:13.311 --> 04:16.223
First there's this one.
Cool, huh?

04:16.781 --> 04:20.728
Yeah, it might make it hard to
strike a really romantic note.

04:21.252 --> 04:23.086
Point taken. Don't despair.

04:23.121 --> 04:26.727
If it's romance we're looking for
I believe I have just the thing.

04:31.796 --> 04:35.266
Yeah, well, there again, she might not
think you had true love on your mind.

04:35.301 --> 04:37.678
Right. Just one more.

04:44.142 --> 04:45.746
True love here I come.

04:51.716 --> 04:55.391
Well, yeah. Yeah,
that's, that's perfect.

04:56.721 --> 05:00.031
Great. Thanks. Wish me luck.

05:00.959 --> 05:02.062
Good luck.

05:07.632 --> 05:09.866
And so it was just
another hopeless Wednesday

05:09.901 --> 05:13.236
as I walked the thousand yards
through the market to work,

05:13.271 --> 05:17.446
never suspecting that this was the day
that was gonna change my life forever.

05:17.875 --> 05:20.855
This is work, by the way,
my little travel bookshop.

05:22.280 --> 05:23.379
Morning, Martin.

05:23.414 --> 05:24.620
Morning, Monseigneur.

05:25.316 --> 05:28.351
Which, well,
sells travel books

05:28.386 --> 05:31.696
and to be frank with you,
doesn't always sell many of those.

05:35.560 --> 05:36.693
Classic.

05:36.728 --> 05:42.109
Profit from major sales push,
minus Â£347.

05:44.669 --> 05:47.438
Shall I go and get
you a cappuccino?

05:47.473 --> 05:49.140
You know, ease the pain a bit.

05:49.175 --> 05:50.540
Yeah. Yeah.

05:50.575 --> 05:53.112
Better make it a half.
All I can afford.

05:54.178 --> 05:56.851
Get your logic.
Demi-cappu coming right up.

06:23.641 --> 06:25.279
Can I help you at all?

06:26.544 --> 06:28.990
No, thanks,
I'll just look around.

06:31.049 --> 06:32.118
Fine.

06:39.724 --> 06:42.125
That book's really not great.

06:42.160 --> 06:46.438
Just in case browsing turned to
buying, you'd be wasting your money.

06:47.699 --> 06:52.170
But if it's Turkey you're interested in,
this one, on the other hand, is very good.

06:53.738 --> 06:57.515
I think the man who wrote it has
actually been to Turkey, which helps.

06:57.809 --> 07:00.619
There's also a very amusing
incident with a kebab

07:01.145 --> 07:03.522
which is one of many
amusing incidents.

07:03.748 --> 07:05.315
Thanks, I'll think about it.

07:05.350 --> 07:08.092
Or, in the bigger
hard-back variety, there's...

07:09.053 --> 07:11.430
I'm sorry,
can you just give me a second?

07:15.526 --> 07:16.629
Excuse me.

07:17.795 --> 07:19.467
Yes?
Bad news.

07:20.331 --> 07:21.597
What?

07:21.632 --> 07:24.578
We've got a security camera
in this bit of the shop.

07:25.136 --> 07:26.202
So?

07:26.237 --> 07:28.876
So I saw you put that
book down your trousers.

07:30.575 --> 07:32.275
What book?

07:32.310 --> 07:33.754
The one down your trousers.

07:35.012 --> 07:37.287
I don't have a book
down my trousers.

07:38.683 --> 07:42.552
Right, I tell you what,
I'll call the police

07:42.587 --> 07:46.090
and what can I say, if I'm wrong about
the whole book- down-the-trousers scenario,

07:46.125 --> 07:47.590
I really apologize.

07:47.625 --> 07:52.039
Okay. What if I did have
a book down my trousers?

07:52.563 --> 07:55.198
Well, ideally,
when I went back to the desk

07:55.233 --> 07:59.070
you'd remove the Cadogan Guide
to Bali from your trousers

07:59.105 --> 08:02.881
and either wipe it
and put it back or buy it.

08:04.075 --> 08:05.679
I'll see you in a sec.

08:06.844 --> 08:08.379
I'm sorry about that.

08:09.280 --> 08:10.554
No, it's fine.

08:11.749 --> 08:14.627
I was gonna steal one
but now I've changed my mind.

08:15.953 --> 08:17.796
Signed by the author, I see.

08:19.557 --> 08:21.324
Yeah, couldn't stop him.

08:21.359 --> 08:24.897
If you can find an unsigned one,
it's worth an absolute fortune.

08:26.364 --> 08:27.764
Excuse me.
Yes?

08:27.799 --> 08:29.539
Can I have your autograph?

08:30.935 --> 08:32.345
Sure.
Here.

08:34.172 --> 08:35.912
What's your name?
Rufus.

08:43.080 --> 08:44.456
What does it say?

08:45.049 --> 08:49.122
That's my signature, and above it, it
says "Dear Rufus, you belong in jail. "

08:49.687 --> 08:50.688
Good one.

08:52.657 --> 08:54.500
Do you want my phone number?

08:55.293 --> 08:58.171
Tempting, but no.

08:59.063 --> 09:00.166
Thank you.

09:03.901 --> 09:05.436
I will take this one.

09:06.137 --> 09:07.303
Oh, right, right.

09:07.338 --> 09:12.014
So, well, on second thoughts
maybe it's not that bad after all.

09:12.977 --> 09:15.389
Actually it's a sort
of classic, really.

09:15.746 --> 09:19.750
None of those childish kebab stories
you find in so many books these days.

09:21.285 --> 09:23.553
I tell you what, I'll throw
in one of those for free.

09:23.588 --> 09:28.469
Useful for lighting fires,
wrapping fish, that sort of thing.

09:32.797 --> 09:34.401
Thanks.
Pleasure.

10:04.629 --> 10:08.668
Here we are.
Cappuccino, as ordered.

10:10.368 --> 10:11.369
Thanks.

10:12.603 --> 10:15.439
I don't think you'll believe
who was just in here.

10:15.474 --> 10:17.816
Who? Was it someone famous?

10:19.510 --> 10:21.677
No, no, no.

10:21.712 --> 10:25.819
Would be exciting though, wouldn't it,
if someone famous came into the shop?

10:26.617 --> 10:32.089
Do you know, this is pretty amazing
actually, but I once saw Ringo Starr.

10:33.090 --> 10:35.426
Where was that?
Kensington High Street.

10:35.461 --> 10:36.492
At least I think it was Ringo.

10:36.527 --> 10:40.064
It might have been that man
from Fiddler On The Roof.

10:40.099 --> 10:41.165
You know, Toppy.

10:41.200 --> 10:42.302
Topol.

10:43.200 --> 10:45.407
Yes, that's right. Topol.

10:48.272 --> 10:51.576
Actually, Ringo Starr doesn't
look at all like Topol.

10:51.611 --> 10:54.283
Yeah, but he was quite
a long way away from me.

10:54.979 --> 10:57.550
So actually it could've
been neither of them?

10:58.449 --> 11:00.087
Yes, I suppose so, yes.

11:01.085 --> 11:02.486
It's not a classic anecdote,
is it?

11:02.521 --> 11:04.397
Not a classic, no. No.

11:09.594 --> 11:11.164
Another one?

11:11.829 --> 11:16.107
Yes. No! Let's go crazy.
I'll have an orange juice.

11:22.773 --> 11:25.082
Okay, thanks. Bye-bye.
See you later.

11:33.317 --> 11:35.302
Shit! Bugger!
Oh, my God!

11:35.337 --> 11:37.288
I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry.

11:37.323 --> 11:38.754
Here let me...

11:38.789 --> 11:39.989
Get your hands off!

11:40.024 --> 11:43.210
I'm really sorry.
I live just over the street.

11:43.245 --> 11:46.222
I have water and soap.
You can get cleaned up.

11:46.257 --> 11:49.200
No, thank you. I just
need to get my car back.

11:49.235 --> 11:50.533
I also have a phone.

11:50.568 --> 11:52.134
I'm confident
that in five minutes

11:52.169 --> 11:54.839
we can have you spick and span
and back on the street again.

11:54.874 --> 11:57.581
In the non-prostitute sense,
obviously.

12:01.278 --> 12:02.381
All right.

12:03.180 --> 12:06.991
Well, what do you mean "just over
the street"? Give it to me in yards.

12:07.318 --> 12:10.788
Eighteen yards. That's my house
there with the blue front door.

12:15.559 --> 12:17.732
Come on in.
I'll just, I'll just...

12:22.900 --> 12:24.310
Right. Right.

12:25.236 --> 12:29.472
Come in. It's not quite as
tidy as it normally is, I fear.

12:29.507 --> 12:34.956
But the bathroom's on the top floor.
And the telephone's just up here.

12:38.015 --> 12:39.391
Here, let me...

12:47.191 --> 12:49.830
Round the corner,
straight on, straight on up.

12:53.631 --> 12:54.632
Bugger!

13:18.022 --> 13:19.757
Would you like a cup
of tea before you go?

13:19.792 --> 13:20.792
No.

13:22.026 --> 13:23.505
Coffee?
No.

13:24.695 --> 13:25.935
Orange juice?

13:27.264 --> 13:28.504
Probably not.

13:29.533 --> 13:31.034
Something else cold?

13:34.638 --> 13:36.139
Coke? Water?

13:37.641 --> 13:39.408
Some disgusting sugary drink

13:39.443 --> 13:41.679
pretending to have something
to do with fruits of the forest?

13:41.714 --> 13:42.680
No.

13:43.080 --> 13:45.116
Would you like
something to eat?

13:45.416 --> 13:49.955
Something to nibble?
Apricots soaked in honey?

13:51.088 --> 13:52.321
Quite why, no one knows,

13:52.356 --> 13:56.736
because it stops them tasting of
apricots and makes them taste like honey,

13:57.495 --> 14:01.465
and if you wanted honey you'd
just buy honey instead of apricots.

14:03.367 --> 14:06.780
But nevertheless, there we go,
they're yours if you want them.

14:07.204 --> 14:08.205
No.

14:11.041 --> 14:13.418
Do you always say
"no" to everything?

14:16.147 --> 14:17.148
No.

14:19.650 --> 14:24.292
I'd better be going.
Thanks for your... help.

14:25.689 --> 14:26.789
You're welcome.

14:26.824 --> 14:31.500
And may I also say... heavenly.

14:33.230 --> 14:34.965
I'll just take my
one chance to say it.

14:35.000 --> 14:36.665
After you've read
that terrible book

14:36.700 --> 14:39.737
you're certainly not gonna
be coming back to the shop.

14:40.538 --> 14:41.641
Thank you.

14:42.940 --> 14:45.920
Yeah, well, my pleasure.

14:57.621 --> 15:01.694
So... it was nice to meet you.

15:03.227 --> 15:05.798
Surreal but nice.

15:08.766 --> 15:09.767
Sorry.

15:18.375 --> 15:20.855
"Surreal but nice. "
What was I thinking?

15:33.424 --> 15:35.028
Hi.
Hi.

15:35.860 --> 15:37.695
I forgot my other bag.

15:37.730 --> 15:39.230
Oh, right. Right.

15:49.373 --> 15:50.374
Thanks.

16:21.839 --> 16:25.582
I'm very sorry about the
"surreal but nice" comment.

16:26.277 --> 16:27.411
Disaster.

16:27.446 --> 16:28.510
That's okay.

16:28.545 --> 16:32.754
I thought the apricot and honey
thing was the real low point.

16:36.153 --> 16:40.567
Oh, my God. My flatmate. I'm
sorry. There's no excuse for him.

16:43.794 --> 16:45.394
Hi.
Hi.

16:45.429 --> 16:47.798
I'm just going into the
kitchen to get some food.

16:47.833 --> 16:49.565
Then I'm gonna tell you
a story that will

16:49.600 --> 16:52.478
make your balls
shrink to the size of raisins.

16:57.608 --> 17:00.179
Probably best not
to tell anyone about this.

17:01.245 --> 17:03.554
Right. Right, no one.

17:04.448 --> 17:07.986
I'll tell myself sometimes but,
don't worry, I won't believe it.

17:15.358 --> 17:16.859
Goodbye.
Bye.

17:29.540 --> 17:32.043
There's something
wrong with this yoghurt.

17:34.244 --> 17:36.981
It's not yoghurt.
It's mayonnaise.

17:37.016 --> 17:38.357
Oh, right. There we are then.

17:41.885 --> 17:43.864
On for a videofest tonight?

17:45.622 --> 17:48.034
I got some absolute classics.

17:51.695 --> 17:53.640
Smile.
No.

17:57.768 --> 17:59.101
Smile.

17:59.136 --> 18:01.377
I've got nothing
to smile about.

18:11.648 --> 18:17.359
Okay, in about seven seconds
I'm going to ask you to marry me.

18:25.596 --> 18:31.045
Imagine... somewhere in the world
there's a man who's allowed to kiss her.

18:34.905 --> 18:40.047
She is... fairly fabulous.

18:49.553 --> 18:51.288
Do you have any
books by Dickens?

18:51.323 --> 18:52.454
No.

18:52.489 --> 18:56.960
No, I'm afraid we're a travel
bookshop. We only sell travel books.

18:58.629 --> 19:01.700
Oh, right. How about the
new John Grisham thriller?

19:03.267 --> 19:06.714
Well, no, because that's
a novel too, isn't it?

19:08.038 --> 19:09.141
Oh, right.

19:13.911 --> 19:15.822
Have you got Winnie-the-Pooh?

19:18.148 --> 19:20.651
Martin, your customer.

19:20.686 --> 19:21.925
Can I help you?

19:34.364 --> 19:35.702
Hey.

19:35.737 --> 19:37.040
Hi.

19:40.771 --> 19:46.983
Just, incidentally,
why are you wearing that?

19:47.678 --> 19:49.623
Combination of factors really.

19:50.481 --> 19:51.513
No clean clothes...

19:51.548 --> 19:55.359
There never will be, you know, unless
you actually clean your clothes.

19:56.120 --> 19:57.894
Vicious circle.
Yeah.

19:58.255 --> 20:02.760
And I was, like, rooting round in your things
and I found this and I thought, "Cool. "

20:04.328 --> 20:06.102
Kinda spacey.

20:10.367 --> 20:12.803
There's something wrong
with the goggles, though.

20:12.838 --> 20:15.180
No, they were prescription.

20:16.140 --> 20:17.339
Groovy.

20:17.374 --> 20:18.909
So I could see all
the fishes properly.

20:19.443 --> 20:21.547
You should do
more of this stuff.

20:21.879 --> 20:23.534
So, look, any messages today?

20:23.569 --> 20:25.189
Yeah, I wrote a couple down.

20:26.483 --> 20:29.327
So there were two, there
were two messages? Right?

20:32.222 --> 20:34.759
You want me to write
down all your messages?

20:35.259 --> 20:39.400
Okay. Who are the ones that
you didn't write down from?

20:41.698 --> 20:43.098
No, gone completely.

20:43.133 --> 20:44.366
Oh, no, there was
one from your mum.

20:44.401 --> 20:47.437
She said don't forget lunch,
and her leg's hurting again.

20:47.472 --> 20:49.712
No one else?
Absolutely no one else.

20:53.076 --> 20:56.680
Though if we're going for this obsessive
writing- down-all-the-message thing,

20:56.715 --> 20:59.626
some American girl called
Anna called a few days ago.

21:05.822 --> 21:06.955
What did she say?

21:06.990 --> 21:08.524
Well, it was genuinely
bizarre.

21:08.559 --> 21:13.804
She said, "Hi, it's Anna. " Then
she said, "Call me at The Ritz. "

21:15.199 --> 21:18.043
And then gave herself
a completely different name.

21:18.235 --> 21:19.601
Which was?

21:19.636 --> 21:21.308
Absolutely no idea.

21:22.306 --> 21:24.239
Remembering one name's
hard enough.

21:24.274 --> 21:28.979
No, I know that. She said that.
I know she's using another name.

21:29.014 --> 21:32.282
The problem is she left
the message with my flatmate

21:32.317 --> 21:34.386
which was a very
serious mistake.

21:36.420 --> 21:38.855
Imagine, if you will, the
stupidest person you've ever met.

21:38.890 --> 21:40.622
Are you doing that?

21:40.657 --> 21:42.759
Yes, sir,
I have him in my mind.

21:42.794 --> 21:43.959
And now double it.

21:43.994 --> 21:48.943
And that is the, what can I say,
the git that I am living with.

21:49.433 --> 21:50.834
And he can't
remember this other...

21:50.869 --> 21:52.404
Try Flintstone.

21:53.303 --> 21:54.403
Sorry. What?

21:54.438 --> 21:56.440
I think she said
her name was Flintstone.

22:00.944 --> 22:03.981
I don't suppose Flintstone
rings any bells, does it?

22:04.016 --> 22:05.549
I'll put you right through,
sir.

22:05.584 --> 22:06.686
Oh, my God.

22:10.787 --> 22:12.732
Hello. Hi.

22:14.925 --> 22:15.994
Hi.

22:16.426 --> 22:20.237
Hi. Sorry.
It's William Thacker.

22:21.732 --> 22:24.075
Yes?
We... I work in a bookshop.

22:24.868 --> 22:28.070
You played it pretty cool there,
waiting for three days to call.

22:28.105 --> 22:31.661
Oh, no, I promise you I've never
played anything cool in my entire life.

22:31.696 --> 22:35.218
My flatmate, who I'll stab to death
later, never gave me the message.

22:37.047 --> 22:38.321
Perhaps

22:39.483 --> 22:42.429
I could drop round for
tea later or something?

22:43.020 --> 22:45.989
Things are pretty busy here.
I might be free around 4:00.

22:46.024 --> 22:48.264
Right. Right. Great.

22:50.193 --> 22:51.194
Bye.

22:57.367 --> 23:05.208
Classic.

23:44.181 --> 23:46.024
Which floor?
Three, please.

24:16.213 --> 24:17.512
Are you sure?

24:17.547 --> 24:19.856
Oh, yeah. Yeah, sure.

24:31.928 --> 24:36.099
Hi. Hi. I'm Karen. I'm sorry,
things are running a little bit late.

24:36.134 --> 24:38.670
Here's the thing.
Do you wanna come this way?

24:40.937 --> 24:42.177
Through here.

24:47.310 --> 24:49.128
So what did you
think of the film?

24:49.163 --> 24:50.912
Yeah, I thought
it was fantastic.

24:50.947 --> 24:54.951
I thought it was Close
Encounters meets Jean de Florette.

24:58.255 --> 24:59.256
I agree.

25:00.557 --> 25:03.126
I'm sorry, I didn't get down
what magazines you're from.

25:03.161 --> 25:04.261
Time Out.

25:04.296 --> 25:05.362
Great.

25:05.796 --> 25:07.172
And you're from?

25:14.171 --> 25:15.581
Horse & Hound.

25:20.410 --> 25:23.947
The name's William Thacker.
Actually, she might be expecting me.

25:23.982 --> 25:26.450
Oh, okay. Take a seat
and I'll go check.

25:30.921 --> 25:34.024
I see you've... I see you've
brought her some flowers.

25:35.258 --> 25:39.137
No. These are
for my grandmother.

25:40.764 --> 25:42.931
She's in a hospital
down the road.

25:42.966 --> 25:45.569
Thought I'd kill two birds
with one stone, you know.

25:45.604 --> 25:47.480
Sure, right. Absolutely, yeah.

25:49.706 --> 25:51.310
Which hospital's that?

25:53.009 --> 25:56.313
Do you mind me not saying? It's a
rather distressing thing, isn't it?

25:56.348 --> 25:57.747
Name of the hospital
kind of gives it away.

25:57.782 --> 25:59.487
Absolutely. Sure.
Cheers.

26:01.585 --> 26:04.454
Right. Mr. Thacker,
if you come this way.

26:04.489 --> 26:05.489
Right.

26:07.524 --> 26:09.230
You've got five minutes.

26:18.668 --> 26:20.408
Hi.
Hello.

26:23.340 --> 26:25.251
I brought these,
but clearly...

26:26.042 --> 26:28.749
No, they're great.
They're great.

26:30.347 --> 26:32.115
I'm sorry about
not ringing back.

26:32.150 --> 26:34.382
The whole "two names" concept

26:34.417 --> 26:37.052
was totally too much for my
flatmate's pea-sized intellect.

26:37.087 --> 26:40.924
No, it's a stupid privacy thing.
I always pick a cartoon character.

26:40.959 --> 26:43.267
Last time I was Mrs. Bambi.

26:47.030 --> 26:48.098
Everything all right?

26:48.133 --> 26:49.297
Yes, thank you.

26:49.332 --> 26:51.368
And you're from Horse & Hound?

26:53.069 --> 26:54.070
Good.

26:55.272 --> 26:56.409
Is that so?

27:04.080 --> 27:05.115
So,

27:10.520 --> 27:13.591
I'll just fire away,
then, shall I?

27:15.825 --> 27:16.928
Right.

27:21.164 --> 27:22.564
The film's great,

27:22.599 --> 27:26.274
and I just was
wondering whether

27:27.504 --> 27:33.750
you ever thought of having
more... horses in it?

27:38.248 --> 27:40.248
Well, we would have liked to,

27:40.283 --> 27:45.323
but it was difficult,
obviously, being set in space.

27:47.157 --> 27:50.137
Space, right, yeah. Yeah,
obviously very difficult.

27:52.362 --> 27:53.695
I'm so sorry.

27:53.730 --> 27:55.730
I arrived outside, they
thrust this thing into my hand.

27:55.765 --> 27:59.035
No, it's my fault. I thought
this would all be over by now.

27:59.070 --> 28:02.305
I just wanted to sort of
apologize for the kissing thing.

28:02.340 --> 28:04.406
I seriously don't know
what came over me.

28:04.441 --> 28:07.512
I just wanted to make sure
that you were fine about it.

28:09.813 --> 28:13.216
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
absolutely fine.

28:15.986 --> 28:19.222
Do remember that Miss Scott is also
keen to talk about her next project

28:19.257 --> 28:21.861
which she is shooting
later in the summer.

28:23.226 --> 28:25.797
Yes, excellent. Excellent.

28:31.901 --> 28:33.539
Any horses in that one?

28:35.338 --> 28:39.513
Or hounds for that matter? Our readers
are equally intrigued by both species.

28:41.678 --> 28:43.623
It takes place on a submarine.

28:45.982 --> 28:47.290
Well, bad luck.

28:48.985 --> 28:53.456
But if there were horses in it

28:54.491 --> 29:00.703
would you be riding them or would you be
getting a stunt-horse-double-man-thing?

29:05.101 --> 29:08.013
I'm a complete moron.
I apologize.

29:08.938 --> 29:10.038
This is very weird.

29:10.073 --> 29:13.543
It's the sort of thing that
happens in dreams, not in real life.

29:14.144 --> 29:20.754
I mean, good dreams. It's a
dream, in fact, to see you again.

29:23.319 --> 29:25.321
What happens next
in the dream?

29:28.425 --> 29:34.030
I suppose that in the dream,
"dream scenario,"

29:34.065 --> 29:37.666
I just change my personality

29:37.701 --> 29:40.443
because you can
do that in dreams

29:43.873 --> 29:48.685
and walk over
and kiss the girl. But...

29:59.289 --> 30:02.167
Time's up, I'm afraid.
Did you get what you wanted?

30:03.960 --> 30:05.026
Nearly, nearly.

30:05.061 --> 30:06.938
Well, maybe just
one last question.

30:08.798 --> 30:10.365
Sure.

30:10.400 --> 30:11.503
Right, right.

30:14.804 --> 30:18.012
Are you busy tonight?

30:19.142 --> 30:20.542
Yes.

30:20.577 --> 30:22.351
Right. Right.

30:25.115 --> 30:26.218
Come in.

30:26.549 --> 30:29.152
Well, it was nice to meet you.

30:29.187 --> 30:30.358
Yes, and you.

30:31.221 --> 30:33.030
Surreal but nice.

30:34.491 --> 30:35.594
Thank you.

30:36.593 --> 30:39.096
You are Horse & Hound's
favorite actress.

30:40.530 --> 30:42.839
You and Black Beauty tied.

30:48.338 --> 30:50.681
Hang on, don't go.
How was she?

30:53.610 --> 30:55.487
Fabulous.
Excellent.

30:55.712 --> 30:58.658
Wait a minute, she took your
grandmother's flowers.

30:59.582 --> 31:03.427
Yeah, yeah.
That's right. Bitch.

31:03.853 --> 31:08.665
Mr. Thacker. If you'd like to come with
me we can just rush you through the others.

31:09.826 --> 31:10.925
The others?

31:10.960 --> 31:12.803
Mr. Thacker is
from Horse & Hound.

31:15.965 --> 31:17.465
How's it going?

31:17.500 --> 31:18.768
Very well. Thank you.

31:18.803 --> 31:19.939
Have a seat.

31:22.539 --> 31:24.450
Well, did you enjoy the film?

31:25.575 --> 31:27.884
Yes. Enormously.

31:28.511 --> 31:30.513
Well, fire away.
Right.

31:32.649 --> 31:34.584
Did you enjoy making the film?

31:34.619 --> 31:35.994
Yes, I did.

31:37.086 --> 31:38.087
Good.

31:39.522 --> 31:41.422
Any bit in particular?

31:41.457 --> 31:44.192
You tell me what
"bit" you enjoyed the most

31:44.227 --> 31:47.003
and I'll tell you if I
enjoyed making that "bit. "

31:51.534 --> 31:54.981
I... liked the bit in space.

31:56.606 --> 31:57.812
Very much.

31:59.475 --> 32:02.353
Did you identify with
the character you're playing?

32:06.015 --> 32:09.752
No.

32:11.387 --> 32:12.388
Oh.

32:14.190 --> 32:15.327
Why not?

32:22.232 --> 32:25.303
Because he's playing a
psychopathic flesh-eating robot.

32:25.902 --> 32:26.903
Classic.

32:28.705 --> 32:33.443
So, is this your first film?

32:33.478 --> 32:35.855
No, it's my 22nd.

32:36.112 --> 32:37.488
Of course it is.

32:38.681 --> 32:40.785
Any favorites among the 22?

32:41.918 --> 32:43.686
Working with Leonardo.

32:43.721 --> 32:44.857
Da Vinci?

32:46.723 --> 32:48.463
DiCaprio.
Of course.

32:51.527 --> 32:54.007
And is he your favorite
Italian director?

32:59.669 --> 33:01.705
Mr. Thacker?
Oh, no.

33:02.739 --> 33:04.650
Have you got a minute?
No.

33:11.648 --> 33:16.653
Hi.

33:21.591 --> 33:24.571
The thing I was doing tonight
I'm not doing anymore.

33:25.228 --> 33:27.965
I told them I had to
spend the evening with

33:28.000 --> 33:30.703
Britain's premiere
equestrian journalist.

33:33.636 --> 33:35.877
Well, great. Fantastic.

33:38.374 --> 33:42.412
Shittity brickity. It's
my sister's birthday. Shit.

33:42.447 --> 33:43.846
We're meant to
be having dinner.

33:43.881 --> 33:45.013
Okay, that's fine.

33:45.048 --> 33:46.848
No, I'm sure
I can get out of it.

33:46.883 --> 33:50.353
No, I mean, if it's fine
with you, I'll be your date.

33:52.088 --> 33:57.128
You'll be my date to my little
sister's birthday party?

33:58.394 --> 34:00.061
If it's all right.

34:00.096 --> 34:01.575
Well, yeah,
I'm sure it's all right.

34:02.098 --> 34:03.431
My friend Max is cooking

34:03.466 --> 34:07.072
and he is generally acknowledged
to be the worst cook in the world,

34:08.737 --> 34:11.407
but you could hide the food
in your handbag or something.

34:11.442 --> 34:14.284
Okay.

34:17.714 --> 34:19.203
He's bringing a girl?

34:19.237 --> 34:20.692
Miracles do happen.

34:21.818 --> 34:23.338
Does the girl have a name?

34:23.373 --> 34:24.858
Don't know, wouldn't say.

34:25.922 --> 34:28.324
Oh Christ,
what is going on in there?

34:29.692 --> 34:31.398
Oh, God!

34:34.397 --> 34:36.536
Hi, come on in.
Vague food crisis.

34:43.206 --> 34:44.405
Hiya.

34:44.440 --> 34:48.444
Sorry, the guinea-fowl is proving
more complicated than expected.

34:49.012 --> 34:50.313
He's cooking guinea-fowl?

34:50.348 --> 34:51.518
Don't even ask.

34:52.315 --> 34:53.315
Hi.
Hi.

34:54.984 --> 34:56.686
Good Lord, you're the
spitting image of...

34:56.721 --> 34:58.563
Bella, this is Anna.

35:00.790 --> 35:02.992
Right.
Okay, crisis over.

35:03.027 --> 35:04.402
Max, this is Anna.

35:05.862 --> 35:07.528
Hi.

35:07.563 --> 35:09.872
Hello, Anna... Scott.

35:11.234 --> 35:13.111
Have some wine.
Thank you.

35:14.837 --> 35:16.008
I'll get it.

35:20.243 --> 35:21.483
Red or white?

35:22.445 --> 35:23.480
Hi.
Hi.

35:25.081 --> 35:26.549
Oh yes, happy birthday.

35:26.584 --> 35:27.648
Thank you.

35:27.683 --> 35:30.319
Look, your brother's
brought this girl...

35:30.354 --> 35:31.695
Hi, guys.

35:32.121 --> 35:33.600
Holy fuck!

35:34.323 --> 35:38.134
Honey, this is Anna. Anna, this
is Honey. She's my baby sister.

35:39.662 --> 35:41.062
Hi.
Oh, God.

35:41.097 --> 35:44.599
This is one of those key moments
in life when it's possible

35:44.634 --> 35:51.278
you can be really genuinely cool
and I'm going to fail just 100%.

35:53.142 --> 35:57.590
I absolutely, totally
and utterly adore you.

35:58.081 --> 36:02.785
And I just think you are the
most beautiful woman in the world.

36:02.820 --> 36:05.520
And more importantly,
I genuinely believe,

36:05.555 --> 36:10.697
and I've believed for some time
now, that we could be best friends.

36:10.960 --> 36:12.632
So what do you think?

36:16.699 --> 36:17.700
Lucky me.

36:20.937 --> 36:22.470
Happy birthday.

36:22.505 --> 36:24.040
Oh, you gave me a present.

36:25.441 --> 36:27.442
We're best friends
already then.

36:27.477 --> 36:30.753
Marry Will, he's a really nice
guy, then we can be sisters.

36:31.214 --> 36:32.852
I'll think about it.

36:34.851 --> 36:36.261
That'll be Bernie.

36:38.588 --> 36:40.822
Hi.
Hi. Sorry I'm late.

36:40.857 --> 36:43.064
Bollocksed up at work again,
I fear.

36:44.227 --> 36:45.394
Millions down the drain.

36:45.429 --> 36:46.429
Well done.

36:46.696 --> 36:47.995
Bernie, this is Anna.

36:48.030 --> 36:49.165
Hello, Anna.
Delighted to meet you.

36:49.200 --> 36:50.331
And you.

36:50.366 --> 36:53.711
Honey bunny,
happy birthday to you.

36:54.137 --> 36:55.809
Hi, Bella.
Hi.

36:57.006 --> 36:59.816
It's a hat. You don't have
to wear it or anything.

37:00.309 --> 37:02.288
Hi, Will.
Hi.

37:03.846 --> 37:04.847
Hi.

37:06.249 --> 37:07.750
Hi.
What?

37:09.085 --> 37:10.427
Wine, Bernie?

37:11.754 --> 37:13.121
You haven't slept with her,
have you?

37:13.156 --> 37:15.658
That is a cheap question and the
answer is, of course, no comment.

37:15.693 --> 37:17.525
No comment means "yes. "
No, it doesn't.

37:17.560 --> 37:19.495
Do you ever masturbate?
Definitely no comment.

37:19.530 --> 37:21.264
You see, it means "yes. "

37:22.498 --> 37:26.571
So, tell me, Anna,
what do you do?

37:28.271 --> 37:30.307
I'm an actress.
Oh, splendid.

37:31.274 --> 37:32.673
What do you do?

37:32.708 --> 37:34.310
I'm actually in the
stock market myself.

37:34.345 --> 37:36.844
So...
not really similar fields.

37:36.879 --> 37:40.053
Though I have done
the odd bit of amateur stuff.

37:41.250 --> 37:44.720
P. G. Wodehouse.
Farce, all that, you know.

37:44.755 --> 37:46.422
"Careful there, vicar. "

37:48.691 --> 37:50.726
Always imagined it's a pretty
tough job, though, acting.

37:50.761 --> 37:53.129
I mean, the wages are
a scandal, aren't they?

37:53.164 --> 37:54.695
They can be.

37:54.730 --> 37:58.334
I see friends from university, clever
chaps, been in the business longer than you.

37:58.369 --> 38:02.077
They're scraping by on seven,
eight thousand a year.

38:03.439 --> 38:04.918
It's no life.

38:05.875 --> 38:07.944
What sort of acting do you do?

38:07.979 --> 38:09.923
Films mainly.

38:10.213 --> 38:14.559
Splendid. Oh, well done.
How's the pay in movies?

38:16.452 --> 38:19.694
I mean, last film you did,
what did you get paid?

38:20.590 --> 38:22.262
$15 million.

38:23.926 --> 38:24.927
Right.

38:26.062 --> 38:29.118
So that's... well, fairly good.

38:29.153 --> 38:32.175
Right, I think we're ready.

38:33.869 --> 38:35.836
Bella, can you tell me
where I can find...

38:35.871 --> 38:38.474
Oh, sorry, yeah, yeah. It's
down the corridor on the right.

38:38.509 --> 38:40.385
I'll show you. I'll show you.

38:43.446 --> 38:45.781
Quickly, quickly, quickly.
Talk very quickly.

38:45.816 --> 38:47.648
What are you doing
here with Anna Scott?

38:47.683 --> 38:50.486
Anna Scott? What, the
film star? Yes. Shut up.

38:50.521 --> 38:51.786
Shh.

38:51.821 --> 38:53.800
Oh, God!
What?

38:54.257 --> 38:55.875
Oh, God. Oh, goddy God.

38:55.910 --> 38:57.458
What did you say to her?

38:57.493 --> 39:00.896
I don't believe it. I don't believe it.
I actually walked into the loo with her.

39:00.931 --> 39:03.499
I was still chatting when she
started unbuttoning her jeans.

39:03.534 --> 39:04.900
She had to ask me to leave.

39:04.935 --> 39:06.033
Oh, God.

39:06.068 --> 39:07.935
So you knew who she was?

39:07.970 --> 39:09.972
Of course I did,
but he didn't!

39:10.840 --> 39:14.651
Well, not instantly,
but I got away with it though.

39:17.913 --> 39:20.188
What do you think
of the guinea-fowl?

39:20.783 --> 39:22.251
I'm a vegetarian.

39:22.286 --> 39:23.422
Oh, God.

39:25.421 --> 39:27.161
So, how's the guinea-fowl?

39:28.791 --> 39:30.964
Best guinea-fowl
I've ever tasted.

40:05.528 --> 40:09.165
Having you here, Anna, firmly
establishes what I've long suspected,

40:09.200 --> 40:12.201
that we really are the most
desperate lot of under-achievers.

40:12.236 --> 40:13.334
Shame.

40:13.369 --> 40:15.036
I'm not saying
it's a bad thing.

40:15.071 --> 40:18.211
In fact, I think it's something
we should take pride in.

40:19.041 --> 40:23.717
I'm gonna give the last brownie
as a prize to the saddest act here.

40:25.581 --> 40:26.649
Bern.

40:28.584 --> 40:30.084
Well, obviously
it's me, isn't it?

40:30.119 --> 40:33.556
I mean, I work in the city
in a job I don't understand

40:33.591 --> 40:36.123
and everyone keeps
getting promoted above me.

40:36.158 --> 40:39.128
I haven't had a girlfriend
since, well, since puberty.

40:39.163 --> 40:41.835
And nobody fancies me.

40:42.431 --> 40:44.433
And if these cheeks get
any chubbier, they never will.

40:44.468 --> 40:46.412
Nonsense. I fancy you.

40:47.703 --> 40:49.079
Really?
Yeah.

40:49.638 --> 40:51.407
Or I did before
you got so fat.

40:51.442 --> 40:52.506
You see.

40:52.541 --> 40:56.712
And unless I'm much mistaken your job
still pays you rather a lot of money

40:56.747 --> 40:58.913
whilst Honey here
earns 20 pence a week

40:58.948 --> 41:01.283
flogging her guts out in
London's worst record store.

41:01.318 --> 41:02.583
Yes!

41:02.618 --> 41:05.286
And I haven't got hair,
I've got feathers.

41:05.321 --> 41:09.166
And I've got funny goggly eyes
and I'm attracted to cruel men.

41:10.025 --> 41:14.897
Actually, no one will marry me because my
boosies have actually started shrinking.

41:14.932 --> 41:16.630
You see,
it's incredibly sad.

41:16.665 --> 41:19.401
Yeah, but on the other hand
her best friend is Anna Scott.

41:19.436 --> 41:22.138
That's true, I can't deny it.
She needs me. What can I say?

41:24.373 --> 41:27.943
And most of her limbs work whereas
I'm stuck in this thing day and night,

41:27.978 --> 41:29.683
in a house full of ramps.

41:29.912 --> 41:32.085
And to add insult
to serious injury

41:33.582 --> 41:36.824
I've totally given up smoking,
my favorite thing.

41:40.489 --> 41:43.834
Well, the truth is,
we can't have a baby.

41:50.666 --> 41:51.837
Oh, Belle...

41:53.536 --> 41:55.015
C'est la vie.

41:58.574 --> 42:01.145
Still, we're lucky
in lots of ways.

42:02.044 --> 42:04.217
But, surely that's
worth a brownie.

42:06.649 --> 42:08.150
Well, I don't know.

42:09.618 --> 42:10.994
Look at William.

42:12.121 --> 42:13.522
Very unsuccessful
professionally.

42:13.557 --> 42:14.641
That's true.

42:14.676 --> 42:15.726
Divorced.

42:16.592 --> 42:19.829
Used to be handsome, now kind
of squidgy round the edges.

42:21.263 --> 42:23.901
And absolutely certain
never to hear from Anna again

42:23.936 --> 42:26.539
once she's heard that his
nickname at school was Floppy.

42:27.136 --> 42:29.411
You did. I can't believe it,
you did.

42:30.439 --> 42:32.139
Thanks very much. Thank you.

42:32.174 --> 42:33.809
Well at least I get
the last brownie, right?

42:33.844 --> 42:35.075
I think so, yes.

42:35.110 --> 42:36.850
Well, wait, what about me?

42:39.381 --> 42:40.484
I'm sorry?

42:41.650 --> 42:43.789
You think you deserve
the brownie?

42:45.421 --> 42:47.039
Well, a shot at it at least,
huh?

42:47.074 --> 42:48.622
Right, well,
you'll have to prove it.

42:48.657 --> 42:52.434
I mean, this is a very, very good
brownie and I'm gonna fight for it.

42:53.596 --> 42:56.474
I've been on a diet
every day since I was 19

42:56.966 --> 43:00.208
which basically means
I've been hungry for a decade.

43:02.004 --> 43:06.008
I've had a series of not nice
boyfriends, one of whom hit me.

43:07.610 --> 43:09.143
And every time
I get my heart broken,

43:09.178 --> 43:14.024
the newspapers splash it about
as though it's entertainment.

43:15.417 --> 43:22.300
And it's taken two rather painful
operations to get me looking like this.

43:22.925 --> 43:24.768
Really?
Really.

43:28.464 --> 43:31.206
And one day, not long from now

43:31.800 --> 43:35.475
my looks will go,
they will discover I can't act

43:36.272 --> 43:41.153
and I will become some sad,
middle-aged woman who

43:42.411 --> 43:45.323
looks a bit like someone
who was famous for a while.

43:54.023 --> 43:56.926
No, nice try, gorgeous,
but you don't fool anyone.

43:58.928 --> 44:01.101
Pathetic effort
to hog the brownie.

44:02.865 --> 44:04.633
Thank you for such
a terrific time.

44:04.668 --> 44:05.770
I'm delighted.

44:07.870 --> 44:09.091
That's a great tie.

44:09.126 --> 44:10.312
Now you're lying.

44:10.573 --> 44:12.841
Okay, it's true. I told you
I was bad at acting.

44:12.876 --> 44:14.043
It was lovely to meet you.

44:14.078 --> 44:15.309
Yeah. And you.

44:15.344 --> 44:18.647
I'll wait until you've gone before
I tell him you're a vegetarian.

44:18.682 --> 44:19.648
No!

44:23.552 --> 44:24.752
Goodnight.

44:24.787 --> 44:26.627
I'm sorry about the loo thing.

44:26.662 --> 44:28.467
I meant to leave but I just...

44:29.358 --> 44:31.327
Look, ring me if you want
someone to go shopping with.

44:31.362 --> 44:32.993
I know lots of nice,
cheap places.

44:33.028 --> 44:35.440
I mean, not that
money is necessarily...

44:35.598 --> 44:37.032
It was just so
nice to meet you.

44:37.067 --> 44:38.300
Happy birthday.
Thank you.

44:38.335 --> 44:39.938
You're my style guru.

44:40.336 --> 44:41.837
Sorry, can I just...

44:43.505 --> 44:44.772
Leave her.

44:44.807 --> 44:46.115
Goodnight, everyone.

44:46.442 --> 44:49.081
Max, Belle, we'll see
you in a couple of days.

44:50.779 --> 44:52.952
Bye, guys.
Bye, Anna.

44:53.949 --> 44:55.249
Love your work.

44:55.284 --> 44:56.888
Goodnight.
Goodnight.

45:04.727 --> 45:07.863
Sorry. They always do that
when I leave the house.

45:07.898 --> 45:11.208
It's a stupid thing.
I hate it.

45:21.977 --> 45:23.477
Floppy, huh?

45:23.512 --> 45:25.355
It's the hair.
It's to do with the hair.

45:29.351 --> 45:31.160
Why is she in a wheelchair?

45:32.287 --> 45:35.859
Because she had an accident
about 18 months ago.

45:36.859 --> 45:39.828
And the pregnancy thing, is
that to do with the accident?

45:39.863 --> 45:40.861
You know, I'm not sure.

45:40.896 --> 45:44.434
