01:32:42.982 --> 01:32:44.392
Well, yeah.

01:32:47.453 --> 01:32:48.693
Groovy.

01:32:50.656 --> 01:32:54.994
Excuse me, are there
any more announcements?

01:32:55.029 --> 01:32:57.094
Well, actually, yes.

01:32:57.129 --> 01:33:01.907
I feel I should apologize to everyone
for my behavior over the last six months.

01:33:02.401 --> 01:33:05.803
I have, as you know, been
somewhat down in the mouth.

01:33:05.838 --> 01:33:08.409
Well, there's an understatement.
There are dead people on better form.

01:33:09.775 --> 01:33:13.446
But I just wish to make it
clear that I've turned a corner,

01:33:13.481 --> 01:33:17.394
and henceforward intend
to be impressively happy.

01:33:38.704 --> 01:33:42.379
Oh, God, I'm horribly drunk.

01:33:43.509 --> 01:33:44.783
Me, too.

01:33:45.211 --> 01:33:46.553
Come here.

01:33:50.750 --> 01:33:52.752
So you've laid the ghost?

01:33:54.921 --> 01:33:56.593
I believe I have.

01:33:56.822 --> 01:33:59.564
Don't give a damn
about the famous girl?

01:34:00.593 --> 01:34:03.630
No. No, I don't think I do.

01:34:05.231 --> 01:34:08.234
Which means you won't be distracted
by the fact that she's back in London,

01:34:08.269 --> 01:34:09.700
grasping her Oscar,

01:34:09.735 --> 01:34:13.774
and currently to be found filming,
most days, on Hampstead Heath.

01:34:14.640 --> 01:34:16.175
Oh, God, no.

01:34:20.112 --> 01:34:22.455
So, not over her, in fact.

01:35:06.158 --> 01:35:08.228
Can I help you?
Yeah.

01:35:09.295 --> 01:35:10.579
I'm looking for Anna Scott.

01:35:10.614 --> 01:35:11.864
Does she know you're coming?

01:35:11.899 --> 01:35:13.164
No.

01:35:13.199 --> 01:35:15.433
No, she doesn't.

01:35:15.468 --> 01:35:17.435
I'm afraid I can't
let you through, sir.

01:35:17.470 --> 01:35:21.941
Right. I mean, I am actually
a friend. I'm not a lunatic.

01:35:23.843 --> 01:35:25.429
But no, you basically...

01:35:25.464 --> 01:35:27.016
Can't let you through, sir.

01:36:08.587 --> 01:36:10.221
Well, this is...

01:36:10.256 --> 01:36:13.100
I only found out
you were here yesterday.

01:36:14.393 --> 01:36:16.062
Well, I was going to call,
but I...

01:36:16.097 --> 01:36:17.298
Anna.

01:36:17.333 --> 01:36:18.499
Yes.

01:36:20.066 --> 01:36:22.101
Things aren't going very well
and it's our last day.

01:36:22.136 --> 01:36:26.060
Absolutely, yeah,
you're clearly very busy.

01:36:26.095 --> 01:36:29.984
But if you could wait,
there are things to say.

01:36:34.947 --> 01:36:36.084
Okay.

01:36:38.451 --> 01:36:41.090
Drink tea.
There's lots of tea.

01:36:48.494 --> 01:36:50.303
Come and have a look.

01:36:54.266 --> 01:36:56.473
Are you a fan of Henry James?

01:36:57.136 --> 01:36:58.637
This is a Henry James film?

01:36:58.672 --> 01:36:59.877
Yeah.

01:37:08.481 --> 01:37:09.613
This is Harry.

01:37:09.648 --> 01:37:13.052
He'll give you a pair of headphones,
so you can hear the dialogue.

01:37:13.087 --> 01:37:14.720
Thank you very much.
No problem.

01:37:14.755 --> 01:37:15.820
Hi.

01:37:15.855 --> 01:37:18.699
Hi, here we go.
Volume's on the side.

01:37:18.824 --> 01:37:20.025
There. Have a seat.

01:37:20.060 --> 01:37:21.128
Thank you.

01:37:29.735 --> 01:37:32.371
We are living in cloud cuckoo land.
We'll never get this done today.

01:37:32.406 --> 01:37:35.007
Well, we've got to. I have
to be in New York on Thursday.

01:37:35.042 --> 01:37:36.679
Stop showing off.

01:37:37.977 --> 01:37:39.812
God, that's an enormous arse.

01:37:39.847 --> 01:37:41.518
I'm not listening.

01:37:41.647 --> 01:37:43.647
No, but seriously,
it's not fair.

01:37:43.682 --> 01:37:46.684
So many tragic young
teenagers with anorexia,

01:37:46.719 --> 01:37:48.888
and that girl has an arse she
could perfectly well share around

01:37:48.923 --> 01:37:52.426
with at least 10 other women,
and still be big bottomed.

01:37:52.892 --> 01:37:54.959
I would think, looking at
something nice like that,

01:37:54.994 --> 01:38:00.967
you and your bony little excuse for an
arse would be well advised to keep quiet.

01:38:02.101 --> 01:38:04.368
Now, down to business,
the end of the scene.

01:38:04.403 --> 01:38:07.748
I ask you when you're telling
everyone, and you say...

01:38:08.908 --> 01:38:11.217
"Tomorrow will be
soon enough. "

01:38:11.510 --> 01:38:14.013
And then I... Right, okay.

01:38:14.613 --> 01:38:18.184
So who was that rather diffident chap
I saw you talking to round the back?

01:38:18.219 --> 01:38:19.390
No one.

01:38:21.487 --> 01:38:23.626
Just some guy from the past.

01:38:24.256 --> 01:38:28.932
It's a bit of an awkward situation
really. I don't know what he's doing here.

01:38:45.244 --> 01:38:46.586
Of course.

01:38:53.319 --> 01:38:55.855
Thanks, I've got to...

01:38:55.890 --> 01:38:57.265
Any time.

01:39:07.800 --> 01:39:11.203
Ladies and gentlemen, can we have
you all on your first marks, please.

01:39:11.238 --> 01:39:12.977
On your first marks.

01:39:26.151 --> 01:39:28.858
I do hate to disturb you
whilst you're cooking the books,

01:39:28.988 --> 01:39:31.331
but there's
a delivery for you.

01:39:32.224 --> 01:39:34.892
Martin, really,
can't you just do it yourself?

01:39:34.927 --> 01:39:38.397
But you see, this is not for
the shop. This is for you.

01:39:40.766 --> 01:39:42.066
Right, okay.

01:39:42.101 --> 01:39:47.050
Now tell me, if I employed a wet rag,
would I have to pay it as much as I pay you?

01:39:50.743 --> 01:39:51.744
Hi.

01:39:53.812 --> 01:39:54.983
Hello.

01:39:55.881 --> 01:39:57.915
You disappeared.

01:39:57.950 --> 01:40:01.069
Yeah. Yeah, I had to leave.

01:40:01.104 --> 01:40:04.189
I didn't want to disturb.

01:40:04.224 --> 01:40:06.258
How have you been?

01:40:06.293 --> 01:40:07.558
Fine. Fine.

01:40:07.593 --> 01:40:09.093
I don't know, everything
much the same, you know.

01:40:09.128 --> 01:40:12.939
When they change the law, Spike
and I will marry immediately.

01:40:13.532 --> 01:40:17.275
Whereas you, I've watched
in wonder. Awards, glory.

01:40:17.569 --> 01:40:21.278
Oh, no, it's all nonsense,
believe me.

01:40:21.874 --> 01:40:26.447
I'd no idea how much nonsense
it was, but nonsense it all is.

01:40:29.782 --> 01:40:33.889
Well, yesterday was
our last day of filming,

01:40:35.321 --> 01:40:36.561
so I'm leaving.

01:40:38.424 --> 01:40:39.630
But...

01:40:42.828 --> 01:40:47.299
I brought this for you from home.
So I thought I'd give it to you.

01:40:50.035 --> 01:40:51.377
Thank you.

01:40:54.006 --> 01:40:55.808
Shall I...
Oh, no, don't open it now,

01:40:55.843 --> 01:40:57.582
I'll be embarrassed.

01:40:59.745 --> 01:41:03.649
Well, thank you. I don't know
what it's for, but thanks anyway.

01:41:03.684 --> 01:41:07.528
I actually had it in my
apartment. I thought you...

01:41:10.522 --> 01:41:12.222
But when it came to it,

01:41:12.257 --> 01:41:15.727
I didn't know how to call,
having behaved so badly.

01:41:16.462 --> 01:41:17.668
Twice.

01:41:19.765 --> 01:41:22.802
So it's just been
sitting in the hotel.

01:41:24.269 --> 01:41:27.875
Then you came,
and I figured...

01:41:32.244 --> 01:41:36.817
The thing is...

01:41:39.685 --> 01:41:41.664
What? What is the thing?

01:41:43.589 --> 01:41:47.126
Don't even think about it.
Go away, immediately. Go away.

01:41:47.161 --> 01:41:49.128
Right. Sorry.

01:41:53.532 --> 01:41:55.170
You were saying?

01:41:57.536 --> 01:41:58.605
Yes.

01:42:01.340 --> 01:42:05.652
I have to go away today,
but I wondered if I didn't,

01:42:07.613 --> 01:42:10.616
whether you might
let me see you a little,

01:42:11.817 --> 01:42:14.559
or a lot, maybe.

01:42:18.223 --> 01:42:20.566
See if you could
like me again.

01:42:21.827 --> 01:42:23.929
But yesterday that actor
asked you who I was

01:42:23.964 --> 01:42:26.602
and you just dismissed
me out of hand.

01:42:27.733 --> 01:42:28.973
I heard.

01:42:30.903 --> 01:42:33.937
You had a microphone,
I had headphones.

01:42:33.972 --> 01:42:36.508
What, you expect me to tell
the truth about my life

01:42:36.543 --> 01:42:39.147
to the most indiscreet
man in England?

01:42:41.513 --> 01:42:44.459
Excuse me. It's your
mother on the phone.

01:42:47.986 --> 01:42:50.454
Will you tell her I'll
ring her back, please?

01:42:50.489 --> 01:42:53.459
I've actually tried that tack, but
she said you've said that once before,

01:42:53.494 --> 01:42:55.359
and it's now been
about 24 hours

01:42:55.394 --> 01:42:58.897
and the foot that was purple is
now sort of blackish in color and...

01:42:58.932 --> 01:43:02.367
Right, right, yeah.
Perfect timing as ever.

01:43:04.736 --> 01:43:07.079
Martin,
hold the fort a second.

01:43:08.841 --> 01:43:10.411
Yes, all right.

01:43:16.915 --> 01:43:22.126
Could I just say, I thought
Ghost was the most wonderful film.

01:43:23.989 --> 01:43:25.524
Is that right?

01:43:25.559 --> 01:43:26.764
Oh, yes.

01:43:31.597 --> 01:43:36.842
I've always wondered what Patrick
Swayze's like in real life.

01:43:38.137 --> 01:43:40.756
I can't say that I know
Patrick all that well.

01:43:40.791 --> 01:43:43.340
What, he wasn't that
friendly during filming?

01:43:43.375 --> 01:43:48.688
Well, I'm sure he was friendly to
Demi Moore who acted with him in Ghost.

01:43:52.918 --> 01:43:54.556
Oh, right. Sorry.

01:43:55.454 --> 01:43:58.491
Right. Always been
a bit of an ass.

01:44:02.094 --> 01:44:05.837
Anyway, well,
it was lovely to meet you.

01:44:05.964 --> 01:44:11.038
I'm a huge fan of yours.
And Demi's of course.

01:44:14.173 --> 01:44:15.845
Sorry about that.

01:44:17.009 --> 01:44:18.142
That's fine.

01:44:18.177 --> 01:44:22.591
There's always a pause when the jury
goes out to consider their verdict.

01:44:24.550 --> 01:44:26.029
Anna, look...

01:44:27.653 --> 01:44:30.030
I'm a fairly
level-headed bloke.

01:44:31.456 --> 01:44:36.462
Not often in and
out of love. But...

01:44:42.301 --> 01:44:47.648
Can I just say "no" to your kind
request, and leave it at that?

01:44:52.277 --> 01:44:53.346
Yes.

01:44:55.881 --> 01:44:57.917
Fine. Of course, I...

01:44:59.284 --> 01:45:00.660
Of course.

01:45:03.255 --> 01:45:06.725
Well, I'll just be going then.
It was nice to see you.

01:45:06.760 --> 01:45:11.970
The thing is,
with you I'm in real danger.

01:45:13.098 --> 01:45:18.172
It seems like a perfect situation,
apart from that foul temper of yours.

01:45:18.437 --> 01:45:22.374
But my relatively
inexperienced heart

01:45:22.409 --> 01:45:24.945
would, I fear, not recover

01:45:25.444 --> 01:45:31.292
if I was once again cast aside,
as I would absolutely expect to be.

01:45:32.050 --> 01:45:35.588
There are just too many
pictures of you, too many films.

01:45:36.421 --> 01:45:41.393
You know, you'd go, and I'd
be well-buggered, basically.

01:45:44.062 --> 01:45:47.202
That really is a real
"no," isn't it?

01:45:47.366 --> 01:45:50.779
I live in Notting Hill.
You live in Beverly Hills.

01:45:51.903 --> 01:45:54.292
Everyone in the world
knows who you are.

01:45:54.327 --> 01:45:56.682
My mother has trouble
remembering my name.

01:45:58.143 --> 01:45:59.314
Fine.

01:46:01.580 --> 01:46:03.354
Fine. Good decision.

01:46:04.683 --> 01:46:06.184
Good decision.

01:46:09.554 --> 01:46:12.899
The fame thing isn't
really real, you know.

01:46:16.895 --> 01:46:19.136
And don't forget,

01:46:20.532 --> 01:46:25.879
I'm also just a girl
standing in front of a boy,

01:46:28.640 --> 01:46:30.551
asking him to love her.

01:46:42.521 --> 01:46:43.590
Bye.

01:47:06.945 --> 01:47:09.414
So, what do you think?
Good move?

01:47:09.449 --> 01:47:11.615
Yeah, good move.

01:47:11.650 --> 01:47:14.753
I mean, when all's said and
done, she's nothing special.

01:47:14.788 --> 01:47:16.153
I saw her taking
her trousers down

01:47:16.188 --> 01:47:19.533
and I definitely glimpsed
some cellulite down there.

01:47:20.292 --> 01:47:24.463
Good decision, yeah. All
actresses are as mad as snakes.

01:47:24.498 --> 01:47:26.048
Tones, what do you reckon?

01:47:26.083 --> 01:47:27.599
Never met her, never want to.

01:47:27.634 --> 01:47:29.366
Brilliant. Max?

01:47:29.401 --> 01:47:31.403
Absolutely.
Never trust a vegetarian.

01:47:31.438 --> 01:47:34.008
Great. Thanks. Brilliant.

01:47:36.942 --> 01:47:38.912
I was called and I came.
What's up?

01:47:38.947 --> 01:47:40.883
William's just turned
down Anna Scott.

01:47:42.114 --> 01:47:45.015
You daft prick.

01:47:45.050 --> 01:47:48.087
No, no. No, no,
it's actually quite sensible.

01:47:51.623 --> 01:47:54.729
That painting
isn't the original, is it?

01:47:56.661 --> 01:47:59.232
You know, I think it might be,
yeah.

01:48:00.766 --> 01:48:03.644
But she said she wanted
to go out with you?

01:48:05.771 --> 01:48:07.404
Yeah.

01:48:07.439 --> 01:48:09.077
Well, that's nice.

01:48:10.642 --> 01:48:11.779
What?

01:48:13.378 --> 01:48:15.612
Well, you know,

01:48:15.647 --> 01:48:19.822
anyone saying they wanna go out
with you is pretty great, isn't it?

01:48:25.690 --> 01:48:30.366
It was sort of sweet,
actually.

01:48:32.164 --> 01:48:36.902
I mean, I know she's an actress and
all that, so she can deliver a line,

01:48:36.937 --> 01:48:42.374
but she said she might be
as famous as she can be

01:48:42.409 --> 01:48:46.344
but also that
she was just a girl,

01:48:48.780 --> 01:48:51.260
standing in front of a boy,

01:48:53.018 --> 01:48:55.555
asking him to love her.

01:49:10.669 --> 01:49:14.139
Oh, sod a dog. I've made the
wrong decision, haven't I?

01:49:18.510 --> 01:49:21.149
Max, how fast is your car?

01:49:24.683 --> 01:49:25.749
Good luck.

01:49:25.784 --> 01:49:28.453
If anyone gets in our way,
we have small nuclear devices.

01:49:28.488 --> 01:49:30.856
Where to? The Ritz. All
I can think is The Ritz.

01:49:30.891 --> 01:49:33.091
Where's Bella?
She's not coming.

01:49:33.126 --> 01:49:35.027
Oh, sod that.
What?

01:49:35.062 --> 01:49:36.928
Bernie, sit in the back.

01:49:38.463 --> 01:49:40.203
Max, I'm okay.

01:49:43.001 --> 01:49:44.536
Come on, baby.

01:49:47.172 --> 01:49:48.707
Mind your back.

01:49:52.978 --> 01:49:54.644
Which way
are you going?

01:49:54.679 --> 01:49:55.912
Down Kensington
Church Street,

01:49:55.947 --> 01:49:57.082
then Knightsbridge,
then Hyde Park Corner.

01:49:57.117 --> 01:49:58.181
No, no, crazy. Crazy.

01:49:58.216 --> 01:50:00.016
Go along Bayswater.
That's right. Then Park Lane.

01:50:00.051 --> 01:50:02.087
No. No. Straight down to the
Cromwell Road, then left.

01:50:02.122 --> 01:50:03.531
No!

01:50:05.457 --> 01:50:08.767
Stop right there! I will
decide the route. All right?

01:50:09.294 --> 01:50:10.670
Sorry, Max.

01:50:12.464 --> 01:50:14.699
James Bond never has to put up
with this sort of shit.

01:50:22.574 --> 01:50:24.809
Turn right. Turn right!
I can't, it's one way.

01:50:24.844 --> 01:50:26.013
Well, do a U-turn.

01:50:26.048 --> 01:50:27.182
Oh, sod it.

01:50:27.312 --> 01:50:28.380
Hold on!

01:50:34.586 --> 01:50:35.928
Brilliant!

01:50:44.329 --> 01:50:46.331
Bloody hell, this is fun.

01:50:47.399 --> 01:50:50.345
Hi. Is Miss Scott
staying here?

01:50:50.468 --> 01:50:51.535
No, sir.

01:50:51.570 --> 01:50:53.413
How about Miss Flintstone?

01:50:54.072 --> 01:50:55.323
No, sir.

01:50:55.358 --> 01:50:56.667
Bambi?

01:50:56.702 --> 01:50:57.941
No, sir.

01:50:57.976 --> 01:51:03.721
Or, I don't know,
Beavis or Butt-head?

01:51:04.249 --> 01:51:05.523
No, sir.

01:51:06.985 --> 01:51:09.362
Thanks. Thanks.

01:51:10.722 --> 01:51:15.102
There was a Miss Pocahontas, but
she checked out about an hour ago.

01:51:15.226 --> 01:51:20.198
I believe she's holding a press conference
at the Savoy, before flying to America.

01:51:25.870 --> 01:51:27.542
We have lift off.

01:51:36.381 --> 01:51:38.622
You have message for Takiama?

01:51:39.451 --> 01:51:41.260
I'll just check, sir.

01:52:03.742 --> 01:52:06.279
Bugger this for
a bunch of bananas.

01:52:10.582 --> 01:52:13.451
Stop! Stop! Stop!

01:52:13.486 --> 01:52:14.986
Go. Go.

01:52:16.988 --> 01:52:22.563
Hang on. Come on. Wait there!
Come on, come on! Wait!

01:52:24.095 --> 01:52:26.131
Go on, go, go, go!

01:52:27.565 --> 01:52:29.100
You're my hero!

01:52:31.636 --> 01:52:33.012
Down, boy.

01:52:43.982 --> 01:52:44.983
Go!

01:52:53.291 --> 01:52:54.924
Excuse me.
Yes, sir?

01:52:54.959 --> 01:52:56.292
Where's the press conference,
please?

01:52:56.327 --> 01:52:58.196
Are you an accredited
member of the press?

01:52:58.231 --> 01:52:59.299
Yeah.

01:53:01.466 --> 01:53:02.799
There you go.

01:53:02.834 --> 01:53:05.954
Yes, that's a Blockbuster
Video membership card, sir.

01:53:05.989 --> 01:53:09.074
That's right. I work for
their in-house magazine.

01:53:09.109 --> 01:53:10.575
Movies Are Our Business.

01:53:10.610 --> 01:53:11.860
I'm sorry, sir.

01:53:11.895 --> 01:53:13.170
He's with me.

01:53:13.205 --> 01:53:14.411
And you are?

01:53:14.446 --> 01:53:18.621
Writing an article on how London
hotels treat people in wheelchairs.

01:53:19.551 --> 01:53:20.750
Yes, of course, madam.

01:53:20.785 --> 01:53:24.892
It's in the Lancaster Room, though
I'm afraid you're rather late.

01:53:25.190 --> 01:53:26.259
Run!

01:53:42.307 --> 01:53:46.411
Does this mean that Miss Scott will
not be publicizing her next film?

01:53:46.446 --> 01:53:48.411
No, it absolutely
does not mean that.

01:53:48.446 --> 01:53:51.549
She'll be abiding by all
her present commitments.

01:53:51.584 --> 01:53:54.652
She just won't be making
any more for the next year.

01:53:54.687 --> 01:53:56.927
When will the
film be released?

01:53:57.055 --> 01:54:00.859
At the moment, the plan is to release
in America towards the end of the autumn,

01:54:00.894 --> 01:54:04.602
and over here, around Christmas,
or early in the New Year.

01:54:04.796 --> 01:54:07.139
Right! Dominic.

01:54:07.365 --> 01:54:10.502
Anna, how much longer are
you staying in the UK then?

01:54:10.537 --> 01:54:12.235
No time at all.
I leave tonight.

01:54:12.270 --> 01:54:16.718
Which is why we have to round things
up now, so final questions, please.

01:54:17.375 --> 01:54:19.013
Yes, lady there.

01:54:19.711 --> 01:54:23.815
Is your decision to take a year off
anything to do with the rumors about Jeff

01:54:23.850 --> 01:54:25.517
and his present leading lady?

01:54:25.552 --> 01:54:27.050
Absolutely not.

01:54:27.085 --> 01:54:28.785
Do you believe the rumors?

01:54:28.820 --> 01:54:32.055
Well, it's really
not my business anymore.

01:54:32.090 --> 01:54:37.938
Though, I will say, from my experience,
rumors about Jeff do tend to be true.

01:54:40.498 --> 01:54:41.631
Yeah.

01:54:41.666 --> 01:54:44.803
The last time you were here, there
were some fairly graphic photographs

01:54:44.838 --> 01:54:48.375
taken of you with
a young English guy.

01:54:49.073 --> 01:54:51.280
So, what happened there?

01:54:51.643 --> 01:54:54.919
He was just a friend.
We're still friends, I think.

01:54:56.714 --> 01:55:00.992
Right. Yes, gentleman
in the pink shirt.

01:55:06.524 --> 01:55:07.593
Yes.

01:55:08.993 --> 01:55:13.900
Miss Scott, are there any
circumstances in which

01:55:13.935 --> 01:55:18.807
the two of you might be
more than just good friends?

01:55:21.506 --> 01:55:26.512
I hoped there would be, but
no, I'm assured there aren't.

01:55:26.644 --> 01:55:27.844
But what would you say if...

01:55:27.879 --> 01:55:29.714
I'm sorry,
just the one question, please.

01:55:29.749 --> 01:55:32.251
No, it's all right.
You were saying?

01:55:34.319 --> 01:55:40.030
I was just wondering if it
turned out that this person...

01:55:41.159 --> 01:55:43.595
Thacker. His name's Thacker.

01:55:43.630 --> 01:55:45.165
Thanks. Thanks.

01:55:45.496 --> 01:55:49.667
I just wondered whether
if Mr. Thacker realized

01:55:49.702 --> 01:55:52.170
he'd been a daft prick

01:55:54.372 --> 01:55:58.276
And got down on his knees
and begged you to reconsider,

01:55:58.311 --> 01:56:03.350
whether you would,
in fact, then reconsider?

01:56:13.591 --> 01:56:15.502
Yes, I believe I would.

01:56:18.830 --> 01:56:20.707
That's very good news.

01:56:23.635 --> 01:56:27.472
The readers of Horse & Hound
will be absolutely delighted.

01:56:33.811 --> 01:56:37.515
Right, Dominic, if you'd like
to ask your question again?

01:56:37.550 --> 01:56:38.516
Yeah.

01:56:38.950 --> 01:56:42.522
Anna, how long are you intending
to stay here in Britain?

01:56:50.295 --> 01:56:51.796
Indefinitely.

01:57:16.220 --> 01:57:17.706
What happened?

01:57:17.741 --> 01:57:19.193
It was good.

01:57:40.745 --> 01:57:42.781
Are you gonna get married?

